<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Online vs Board Scrabble</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Word of the Day · Dictionary</p>


    <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
      <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
      <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
      <span>7 min read</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Whether you play on a wooden board with family or compete online against strangers worldwide, Scrabble is the same game at its core. But the format changes the experience in meaningful ways — from timing and etiquette to available tools and social dynamics. Here's an honest comparison to help you get the most from both.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Pros & Cons: Side by Side</h2>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🖥️ Online Scrabble — Pros</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Play anytime, anywhere, any opponent · Auto-scoring eliminates errors · Instant word validation (no disputes) · Rated games track progress · Post-game analysis built in</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
        <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🖥️ Online Scrabble — Cons</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">No physical social interaction · Screen fatigue in long sessions · Temptation to use external tools · Less tactile satisfaction · Can feel impersonal</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎲 Board Scrabble — Pros</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Face-to-face social bonding · Tactile tile placement · Read opponent body language · No screen time required · Full physical tile tracking</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
        <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎲 Board Scrabble — Cons</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Need a willing opponent nearby · Manual scoring causes errors · Challenge disputes need dictionary · Setup and cleanup time · Limited to local players</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Key Differences in Rules & Timing</h2>

